by measuring their response
to visual stimuli.

278
00:11:50,874 --> 00:11:52,340
So, goofing off.

279
00:11:54,910 --> 00:11:57,579
As I was saying, I'm done
with work and Leonard's not.

280
00:11:57,581 --> 00:12:00,215
So good news,
you get to take me home.

281
00:12:00,217 --> 00:12:01,249
Play your cards right,

282
00:12:01,251 --> 00:12:02,751
I'll let you drive me

283
00:12:02,753 --> 00:12:05,837
past the lot
where the buses park at night.

284
00:12:05,839 --> 00:12:07,639
I can't leave now, Sheldon.

285
00:12:07,641 --> 00:12:08,757
I'm very busy.

286
00:12:08,759 --> 00:12:10,558
Besides, why would I want
to do you a favor

287
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,577
after the way you treated
me in the cafeteria?

288
00:12:12,579 --> 00:12:15,129
Image number four:
boa constrictor.

289
00:12:18,968 --> 00:12:21,936
What on earth
are you talking about?

290
00:12:21,938 --> 00:12:23,488
My behavior
in the cafeteria

291
00:12:23,490 --> 00:12:25,306
was delightful.

292
00:12:25,308 --> 00:12:27,492
Maybe your friend
Gunderson needs

293
00:12:27,494 --> 00:12:29,444
to head over
to IKEA and assemble

294
00:12:29,446 --> 00:12:32,380
a sense of humor.

295
00:12:32,382 --> 00:12:34,365
You embarrassed me
in front of my colleagues

296
00:12:34,367 --> 00:12:35,983
on my first day here.

297
00:12:36,685 --> 00:12:37,786
Image number five:

298
00:12:37,788 --> 00:12:39,187
kitten in a teacup.

299
00:12:39,189 --> 00:12:41,389
Oh.

300
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,529
Oh... embarrassed you?
You know what?

301
00:12:47,531 --> 00:12:50,432
I don't have time for this.
Find another way home.

302
00:12:50,434 --> 00:12:53,451
I'm starting to get the sense
that you're angry with me.

303
00:12:53,453 --> 00:12:55,002
Really?
What tipped you off?

304
00:12:55,004 --> 00:12:56,054
Couple things, actually.

305
00:12:56,056 --> 00:12:57,171
Your tone of voice,
your body language...

306
00:12:57,173 --> 00:12:58,807
Get out.
Well, now, that.

307
00:13:00,676 --> 00:13:03,311
Image number six:
woman giving birth.

308
00:13:12,571 --> 00:13:14,188
It's 9:00.
Where you been?

309
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:17,308
Oh, I had to take
the bus home.

310
00:13:17,310 --> 00:13:20,845
Fell asleep and missed my stop.

311
00:13:20,847 --> 00:13:22,647
Oh, no.

312
00:13:22,649 --> 00:13:26,634
Did you know that Los Angeles
has a Little Sri Lanka?

313
00:13:26,636 --> 00:13:28,987
I did not.

314
00:13:28,989 --> 00:13:31,005
Well, I do... now.

315
00:13:31,007 --> 00:13:33,708
They're a lovely people.

316
00:13:33,710 --> 00:13:37,378
Although terrifying when you
wake up face-to-face with them.

317
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:39,647
If you're hungry, I brought home

318
00:13:39,649 --> 00:13:41,633
some mutton and coconut milk.

319
00:13:41,635 --> 00:13:43,618
Why'd you get that?
You hate lamb.

320
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:45,687
I was asking for directions.

321
00:13:45,689 --> 00:13:49,207
Apparently, there was
a communication problem.

322
00:13:49,209 --> 00:13:52,327
I thought Amy was gonna
drive you home.

323
00:13:52,329 --> 00:13:53,611
Yeah, I thought so, too,

324
00:13:53,613 --> 00:13:55,780
but she's acting very strangely.

325
00:13:55,782 --> 00:13:58,783
I was discussing it with
a Sri Lankan fellow on the bus,

326
00:13:58,785 --> 00:14:01,870
and he hypothesized
that a tiger may have

327
00:14:01,872 --> 00:14:04,055
recently run across her shadow.

328
00:14:05,908 --> 00:14:08,343
Although he may have just been
trying to drum up business

329
00:14:08,345 --> 00:14:11,346
for his brother-in-law's
witch doctor practice.

330
00:14:14,266 --> 00:14:16,835
Okay, Sheldon, what happened
between you and Amy?

331
00:14:16,837 --> 00:14:20,572
Well, can you believe
she said I embarrassed her?

332
00:14:20,574 --> 00:14:22,657
Yeah.

333
00:14:22,659 --> 00:14:25,443
But you didn't
even hear the details.

334
00:14:25,445 --> 00:14:27,478
Sheldon...

335
00:14:29,248 --> 00:14:31,866
I've known you
a long time,

336
00:14:31,868 --> 00:14:33,284
and I'm going
to tell you this

337
00:14:33,286 --> 00:14:37,155
with all the love
I can possibly muster.

338
00:14:37,157 --> 00:14:38,156
Amy's right.

339
00:14:38,158 --> 00:14:39,607
You're wrong.

340
00:14:40,459 --> 00:14:41,659
But you don't even know...

341
00:14:41,661 --> 00:14:43,077
Doesn't matter.

342
00:14:43,079 --> 00:14:45,697
But, now, but in my defense...
Doesn't matter.

343
00:14:45,699 --> 00:14:47,932
You're not listening
to my side of it.

344
00:14:47,934 --> 00:14:50,268
Okay, fine, Sheldon.
What is your side?

345
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:52,286
Well...

346
00:14:52,288 --> 00:14:54,789
Nope, got to go with
Amy on this one.

347
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:01,679
Shrimp was spicy.

348
00:15:01,681 --> 00:15:03,114
You want a TUMS?

349
00:15:03,116 --> 00:15:04,432
You got
the tropical fruit kind?

350
00:15:04,434 --> 00:15:06,951
No, if I buy those, I just
go through them like candy.

351
00:15:06,953 --> 00:15:08,386
Tell me about it.

352
00:15:08,388 --> 00:15:11,105
One time, I swear
I pooped out a stick of chalk.

353
00:15:13,142 --> 00:15:15,360
I'll get it.
Thanks.

354
00:15:17,279 --> 00:15:18,363
Hi.

355
00:15:18,365 --> 00:15:19,530
Oh, hi.

356
00:15:19,532 --> 00:15:21,699
I may have overreacted.

357
00:15:21,701 --> 00:15:25,620
Yeah, well, I didn't
handle it so great, either.

358
00:15:25,622 --> 00:15:28,039
It's just sometimes I feel
like you enjoy spending time

359
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:30,091
with your friends
more than with me.

360
00:15:30,093 --> 00:15:31,910
That's not true.
It's not?

361
00:15:31,912 --> 00:15:33,595
You spend all day
together at work,

362
00:15:33,597 --> 00:15:35,713
and then you all hang out
at night playing games,

363
00:15:35,715 --> 00:15:37,231
going to the comic book store.

364
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:39,851
Last week, you two got
a couples massage.

365
00:15:42,488 --> 00:15:45,056
So, when you said you wouldn't
want to spend that much time

366
00:15:45,058 --> 00:15:48,026
with me, it really
hurt my feelings.

367
00:15:48,028 --> 00:15:49,644
Oh, wow.

368
00:15:49,646 --> 00:15:50,979
Yeah, no, I get that.

369
00:15:50,981 --> 00:15:52,113
I'm so sorry.

370
00:15:52,115 --> 00:15:54,866
Starting tomorrow, I am
turning over a new leaf.

371
00:15:54,868 --> 00:15:57,986
Time with you is my
number one priority.

372
00:15:59,990 --> 00:16:01,689
Why tomorrow?

373
00:16:03,191 --> 00:16:05,510
Well, we're real close
to finishing off

374
00:16:05,512 --> 00:16:07,378
the new Batman game.

375
00:16:08,514 --> 00:16:11,666
It is awesome.

376
00:16:13,969 --> 00:16:16,004
Uh, you should probably
go after her.

377
00:16:16,006 --> 00:16:17,755
Should I go after you?

378
00:16:17,757 --> 00:16:19,924
No!

379
00:16:21,593 --> 00:16:24,095
Thanks for getting me
in trouble.

380
00:16:26,899 --> 00:16:28,266
Amy.

381
00:16:29,068 --> 00:16:30,284
Amy.

382
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:33,104
Amy.

383
00:16:34,723 --> 00:16:37,325
Sheldon, what are you
doing here so late?

384
00:16:37,327 --> 00:16:39,193
I couldn't sleep
because I kept thinking

385
00:16:39,195 --> 00:16:41,446
about what happened
earlier between us.

386
00:16:42,247 --> 00:16:45,616
Also, I had one heck
of a bus nap.

387
00:16:46,752 --> 00:16:47,902
Oh, speaking of which,

388
00:16:47,904 --> 00:16:50,788
do you want some mutton
and coconut milk?

389
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:51,856
No.

390
00:16:51,858 --> 00:16:54,625
Well, I cannot give
this stuff away.

391
00:16:54,627 --> 00:16:57,078
What do you want?

392
00:16:57,080 --> 00:17:00,648
Amy, this isn't easy to say.

393
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:04,752
All relationships are difficult,

394
00:17:04,754 --> 00:17:07,689
but even more so
when you're in one

395
00:17:07,691 --> 00:17:09,524
with a person who struggles

396
00:17:09,526 --> 00:17:11,859
with everyday
social interactions.

397
00:17:11,861 --> 00:17:13,528
And frankly...

398
00:17:13,530 --> 00:17:15,146
who can strike some people

399
00:17:15,148 --> 00:17:17,665
as being kind of a weirdo.

400
00:17:17,667 --> 00:17:19,650
Sheldon...

401
00:17:19,652 --> 00:17:21,652
you're not a weirdo.

402
00:17:21,654 --> 00:17:24,272
I wasn't speaking about me.

403
00:17:26,308 --> 00:17:28,442
I mean, honestly,
there's no telling

404
00:17:28,444 --> 00:17:30,078
what will set you off.

405
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:32,296
You know, introducing
myself as your boyfriend.

406
00:17:32,298 --> 00:17:35,550
Giving you the opportunity
to drive me home.

407
00:17:35,552 --> 00:17:37,618
Breaking the ice
with your colleagues

408
00:17:37,620 --> 00:17:40,788
using ethnic humor,
the funniest kind of humor.

409
00:17:42,558 --> 00:17:44,225
What's your point?

410
00:17:44,227 --> 00:17:46,627
My point is, we're a couple.

411
00:17:46,629 --> 00:17:48,362
And...

412
00:17:48,364 --> 00:17:50,481
I like you for who you are.

413
00:17:50,483 --> 00:17:52,366
Quirks and all.

414
00:17:54,103 --> 00:17:55,653
I like you, too.

415
00:17:55,655 --> 00:17:58,189
Well, I should hope so.

416
00:17:58,191 --> 00:18:00,324
I don't see anyone else
banging on this door

417
00:18:00,326 --> 00:18:02,827
to put up with your nonsense.

418
00:18:06,982 --> 00:18:09,584
Not even a good-bye?

419
00:18:09,586 --> 00:18:11,085
You see,
that's the kind of thing

420
00:18:11,087 --> 00:18:13,621
that makes people
think you're weird.

421
00:18:13,623 --> 00:18:15,423
Poor kid.

422
00:18:15,425 --> 00:18:17,508
She just doesn't see it.

423
00:18:27,609 --> 00:18:28,692
I'm not apologizing
to Howard.

424
00:18:28,694 --> 00:18:30,343
He can come beg me
on his knees.

425
00:18:30,345 --> 00:18:31,695
Sheldon, too.

426
00:18:31,697 --> 00:18:34,197
If I see him at work,
I'm just going to ignore him.

427
00:18:34,199 --> 00:18:36,033
All right, don't worry.
I talked to Leonard.

428
00:18:36,035 --> 00:18:38,802
He is gonna sit the guys down
and set them straight.

429
